-- Russia May Sell $700 Million a Day to Support Ruble If Oil Falls
-- B y   A r t y o m   D a n i e l y a n
-- 2012-06-06T09:33:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-06/russia-may-sell-700-million-a-day-to-support-ruble-if-oil-falls.html
Russia ’s central bank may have to
sell as much as $700 million of foreign currency a day to
support the ruble if oil prices continue to fall, Chairman
Sergey Ignatiev said in St. Petersburg today.  Bank Rossii has sold about $200 million a day in the last
three days to halt the ruble’s decline, Ignatiev said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
